      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1989 Porsche 911 Carrera 3.2 represents the pinnacle of the air-cooled G-series, featuring the definitive Getrag G50 five-speed manual transaxle and a factory-correct 3.2L flat-six engine. The powertrain is mechanically superlative, exhibiting zero oil migration from the crankcase and a valvetrain that operates with surgical precision. Performance is managed by a flawlessly mapped Bosch Motronic system, ensuring crisp throttle response across the power band. The chassis retains its original geometric integrity, supported by a pristine torsion bar suspension and staggered Fuchs forged alloys. This specimen is devoid of synchro wear or bushing fatigue, offering a communicative driving experience that is increasingly rare. A concours-level example for the technically-minded collector.",
